entry.title: Local Government Act (Northern Ireland) 1923
entry.summary: An Act to amend the Law relating to Local Government in Northern Ireland, and for purposes connected therewith.

entry.title: Universities of Oxford and Cambridge Act 1923
entry.summary: An Act to make further provision with respect to the Universities of Oxford and Cambridge and the Colleges therein.

entry.title: Agricultural Credits Act 1923
entry.summary: An Act to facilitate the advance of money and the grant of credit for certain agricultural purposes, and to amend the Improvement of Land Act, 1864, and for purposes connected therewith.

entry.title: Alderney (Transfer Of Property, &c.) Act 1923
entry.summary: An Act to provide for the transfer of certain property, rights, duties and liabilities in or in connection with the Island of Alderney.

entry.title: War Memorials (Local Authorities’ Powers) Act 1923
entry.summary: An Act to enable local authorities under certain circumstances to maintain, repair and protect war memorials vested in them.

entry.title: Explosives Act 1923 (repealed)
entry.summary: An Act to amend the Explosives Act 1875,

entry.title: Mines (Working Facilities and Support) Act 1923
entry.summary: An Act to make provisions for facilitating the working of minerals and for imposing restrictions on the working of minerals required for the support of railways, buildings and works.

entry.title: Double Taxation Relief Act (Northern Ireland) 1923
entry.summary: An Act to give the force of Law to the consent of the Government of Northern Ireland to certain arrangements for Relief in respect of Double Taxation as between Northern Ireland and the Irish Free State.

entry.title: Public Records Act (Northern Ireland) 1923
entry.summary: An Act to establish a Public Record Office of Northern Ireland for the reception and preservation of certain public records appertaining to Northern Ireland, and for purposes connected therewith.

entry.title: Special Constables Act 1923
entry.summary: An Act to make perpetual, subject to an amendment, the Special Constables Act 1914; to provide for the employment of special constables in connection with Naval, Military and Air Force yards and stations; and to remove certain limitations on the appointment of special constables in Scotland.

entry.title: Industrial Assurance Act 1923 (repealed )
entry.summary: An Act to consolidate and amend the law relating to Industrial Assurance, and to make provision with respect to war bond policies and policies to which the Courts (Emergency Powers) Act 1914, applies, and bond investment business.

entry.title: Criminal Evidence Act (Northern Ireland) 1923
entry.summary: An Act to amend the Law of Evidence in its application to Northern Ireland.

entry.title: Criminal Law Amendment Act (Northern Ireland) 1923
entry.summary: An Act to amend the law in Northern Ireland with respect to offences against persons under the age of sixteen, and with respect to penalties under section thirteen of the Criminal Law Amendment Act, 1885.

entry.title: Fees (Increase) Act 1923 (repealed 1.5.1994)
entry.summary: An Act to provide for the increase of certain fees and the imposition of certain new fees in respect of various services, and for purposes connected therewith.

entry.title: Railway Fires Act (1905) Amendment Act 1923
entry.summary: An Act to amend the Railway Fires Act, 1905.

entry.title: Irish Free State (Consequential Provisions) Act 1922
entry.summary: An Act to make such provisions as are consequential on or incidental to the establishment of the Irish Free State.

entry.title: Finance Act (Northern Ireland) 1922
entry.summary: An Act to amend the Law relating to certain Duties of Inland Revenue (including Excise) and to alter other Duties payable in Northern Ireland.

entry.title: Uniformity of Laws Act (Northern Ireland) 1922
entry.summary: An Act to apply to Northern Ireland certain Acts passed by the Parliament of the United Kingdom in the present Session thereof.

entry.title: Revised Tables of Lessons Measure1922
entry.summary:
A Measure passed by the National Assembly of the Church of England
To amend the Law relating to the Tables of Lessons contained in the Prayer Book.

entry.title: Celluloid and Cinematograph Film Act 1922
entry.summary: An Act to make better provision for the prevention of fire in premises where raw celluloid or cinematograph film is stored or used.
